    public class BainNN

    • Constructor Detail

      • BainNN

        public BainNN(ojc.bain.NeuralNetwork nn,
      int[] outputDimensions,
      int stepsPerStep,
      boolean feedForward)
        Create a new BainNN with the given Bain neural network.
        Parameters:
        nn - The Bain neural network to use.
        outputDimensions - The size of each dimension in the output. At the moment only one or two dimensional output vectors are supported, so this array should only be of length one or two accordingly. Dimensions should be in the order x, y.
        stepsPerStep - The number of simulation steps to perform in the Bain neural network for each call to next(..) or nextSequence(..) methods. For feed-forward networks this should be equal to the number of layers.
        feedForward - Indicates if the network topology is strictly feed-forward. This is used to optimise execution of the nextSequence(double[][]) and nextSequence(double[][][]) methods.

      • BainNN

        public BainNN(ojc.bain.NeuralNetwork nn,
      int[] outputDimensions,
      int stepsPerStep,
      boolean feedForward,
      java.lang.String name)
        Create a new BainNN with the given Bain neural network.
        Parameters:
        nn - The Bain neural network to use.
        outputDimensions - The size of each dimension in the output. At the moment only one or two dimensional output vectors are supported, so this array should only be of length one or two accordingly. Dimensions should be in the order x, y.
        stepsPerStep - The number of simulation steps to perform in the Bain neural network for each call to next(..) or nextSequence(..) methods. For feed-forward networks this should be equal to the number of layers.
        feedForward - Indicates if the network topology is strictly feed-forward. This is used to optimise execution of the nextSequence(double[][]) and nextSequence(double[][][]) methods.
        name - A name for this BainNN.
